A draft regulation for public comment has been published in the provincial government gazette. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Department of Transport and Public Works plans to increase motor vehicle licence fees by an average of 6%. A draft regulation for public comment has been published in the provincial government gazette. Comments from motor vehicle owners can also be delivered at the department s offices.Spokesperson for the Provincial Transport MEC Siphesihle Dube said: We are not required by law to publish them for public comment but we have done so because in excess of 1.7 million vehicle owners in the Western Cape must have an opportunity to submit comments on it. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)